full_content:
Article 155
Serious Injury is:
a.

illness or injury for which there is no hope of complete recovery or which may cause death;

b.

are constantly incapable of performing their duties, positions or work;

c.

unable to use any of the five senses or any of the body’s limbs;

d.

severe disability or permanent disability;

e.

paralyzed;

f.

disturbed thinking power for more than 4 (four) weeks;

g.

miscarriage or stillbirth; or

h.

impaired reproductive function.

