full_content:
Article 83
(1) Immigration Officials have the authority to place a Foreigner in an Immigration Detention Center or Immigration Detention Room if the Foreigner:
a. are in Indonesian Territory without having a valid Stay Permit or having a Stay Permit that is no longer valid;
b. are in Indonesian Territory without having valid Travel Documents;
c. subject to Immigration Administrative Action in the form of cancellation of Residence Permit for committing acts that are contrary to statutory regulations or disrupt security and public order;
d. awaiting deportation; or
e. waiting for departure outside the Indonesian Territory because the Entry Certificate was refused.
