full_content:
Article 106
Immigration PPNS has the authority to:
a. receive reports regarding immigration crimes;
b. seek information and evidence;
c. take the first action on the scene;
d. prohibit anyone from leaving or entering the crime scene for investigation purposes;
e. summon, examine, search, arrest, or detain someone suspected of committing an immigration crime;
f. detain, examine and confiscate Travel Documents;
g. order a suspected person or suspect to stop and check his or her identity;
h. examine or confiscate letters, documents or objects related to immigration crimes;
i. summon someone to be questioned and hear their statement as a suspect or witness;
j. bringing in the necessary experts in connection with the case examination;
k. carry out inspections at certain places where it is suspected that there are letters, documents or other objects related to immigration crimes;
l. taking photos and fingerprints of suspects;
m. request information from the public or competent sources;
n. terminate the investigation; and/or
o. carry out other actions according to law.

